Minister of Information and Culture, Lai Mohammed, has refused to disclose the actual date that President Muhammadu Buhari will return to the country from London, United Kingdom.  Buhari left the country on March 30 for what the Presidency described as routine medical check-up in London.  The Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity, Femi Adesina, had in a statement said Buhari was due back in the country during the second week of April, 2021. See Also






